page.title: 09PARTRIDGE GREEN ECOLOGY
page.content: We,LYNDA DEANS and NATALIE JONES,interviewed two of the village's residents,MR.HUTTON and MR.HIGGINS,who are very interested in local trees,birds and wildlife.On his walks along the now disused railway line to Henfield MR.HIGGINS sees foxes,slow worms,vipers badgers,moles,rabbits and squirrels.MR.HUTTON is a keen bird-spotter and sees nightingales,barnowls,cuckoos and the summer migrants from Africa house martins and swallows.The commonest trees in the area,many found around THE PARK,are the beech and oak trees and the oldest tree of over 100 years of age is the cedar.
